        <bioghist>
            <p>Public School 22 originally was located at 2833 Main St., but moved in 1920 to
Huntington Ave. near Beard Ave. The school was closed ca. 1981.</p>
        </bioghist>
        
        <scopecontent>
            <p>Notebook of Mother's Club, 1922-1927; treasurer's notebook, minute books, and
scrapbook of the Parent-Teachers Association, 1925-1941; inventory of Department of Industrial Arts, 1935-1948;
minute books of Hospitality Club, 1949-1962; guest book pages, 1979; lists of Ketchum Medal winners, 1927-1947;
and several reminiscences, ca. 1971.</p>
        <arrangement>
                <p>Organized by format into two series: I. Notebooks. II. Other materials. Chronological arrangement
within series.</p>
            </arrangement>
        </scopecontent>
